<br>
1) The ogres are not very good ship builders.  Has anyone gotten a good look at the &quot;Bloated Belly&quot;? It looks like they found a wrecked ship, stuck it on a few rotten boards, then added barrels for boyancy.<br>
<br>
2) Despite what the everquest map book says, the monsters in the Dreadlands are NOT levels 1-10.<br>
<br>
3) Drachnids can see through hide (though they seem to have a small visual range). I suspect it's because they are half spiders. I've always known that spiders could see through hide (go ahead, prove me wrong).<br>
<br>
4) That tunnel in the Dreadlands is pretty.<br>
<br>
Of course, I did learn new languages when the Faire started. I am now master of Troll, Ogre, and Elder Teir'Dal in addition to what I already knew.  I also taught a few people Halfling.  Next time though, I will try to ask for a port (unless I get Luclin by then). <p>Xaedria<br>
